        <para>
            When you log in, changes occur both in the buttons above and in the folders below.
        </para>
        <para>
            In order to log in to the Tamboti framework, use the username and password you use to access the Cluster IT resources. 
        </para>
        <para>
            When you click on the "Login" sign in the upper right corner, a pop-up window will appear. Enter the part of your username before "@ad.uni-heidelberg.de".
        </para>
        <para>As password, enter the password you use to access IT Cluster resources. Your password is not stored in the database, but sent to the Heidelberg University Active Directory to be authenticated.
        </para>
        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/walk-through.09.1.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>
        </para>
        <para>
            After logging in, you will see that the username you are logged in under in the upper right corner, with an option to log out again. </para>
        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/walk-through.09.2.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>
        </para>
        <para>Your session lasts 30 minutes. You are presented with a warning that you will be logged out after 30 minutes of inactivity. If you do not respond to this within five minutes, your session will expire. This means that whatever you have not finished in the editor will be lost. It also means that your list in My List will be lost.
        </para>
